**Decomposition Module 6: Assembly Line Designer** (final module!)

Henry Ford broke car-building into simple repeatable steps. Same idea works for software **processes** — break a big workflow into specialized stations.

**Assembly line → software:**

| Manufacturing | Software |
|---|---|
| Specialized stations | Microservices (one job each) |
| Standard interfaces | APIs / data contracts |
| Quality checkpoints | Testing / validation |
| Parallel production lines | Concurrent processing |
| Inventory buffers | Queues / caching |
| Optimization metrics | Performance monitoring |

---

## Challenge 1: User Registration Assembly Line

**The monolith ("artisan workshop"):** one giant function does everything:

```
function registerUser(userData) {
    // validate input
    // check if email exists
    // hash password
    // create user record
    // send welcome email
    // log user in
    // create default preferences
    // send analytics event
    // return success
}
```

**Your task — redesign it as an assembly line:**

1. Which steps **must run in order** (sequential stations)? List them.
2. Which steps **can run in parallel** (independent lines) once the user exists?

Hint: things like saving the user must happen before sending a welcome email — but the welcome email, analytics event, and preferences could all run at the same time.

Type your sequential vs. parallel split when you're ready.

